    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-20T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-20T10:00:00-05:00" n="317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00B/12–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-20T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 20, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4434. Personal for the Secretary only. If you have not already done so, I
                    strongly recommend that you read top secret memorandum No. 345, November 23<note
                        n="82" xml:id="d317fn82">Marginal notation in Secretary Byrnes’ handwriting:
                        “Let me have this.”</note> written by Chipman, Paris, entitled “Tactics of
                    the French Communist Party according to a source maintaining close contacts with
                    important Communists”.<note n="83" xml:id="d317fn83">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_471">p. 471</ref>.</note> On
                    basis of our analysis <pb facs="0497" n="479" xml:id="pg_479"/> here, I consider
                    this to be most accurate revealing exposé of present Soviet tactics not only in
                    France but throughout rest of Europe and to be principal explanation for
                    ultimate concessions made at <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> and
                    Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
